INSERT INTO `text_content` VALUES (4,'Project will have direct link to a dashboard.'),(6,''),(10,'A domain model is located in an sd-domain layer. This layer is meant to be plain old java \nobjects (POJO). Location in the layered view is slightly non standard. Even though it exists \non same level as many others, it cannot depend basically on any other layers. It is logically \nshowing that domain model usage is spread all around Shared Design Tool including the \nserver side. As long as there are no complex dependencies in the domain model it can be \nused on the client and the server side. \n\n'),(11,'In Figure a dashed line separates client and server sides. As described in RIA, rich \nweb applications have limitations during the implementation. In GWT those limitations \nare that the client can depend only GWT emulated Java libraries and classes implemented\n5 Shared Design Tool Design and Implementation 37 \nin those libraries. If some unknown dependency is added, there will be a run time failure \nof loading those classes in the GWT development environment. '),(13,'Shared Design Tool application framework was extracted from main application code \nto have more reusable code. It could have been just Java packages inside the sd-app, \nbut this also restrict that component wouldn’t accidentally have unwanted dependencies \nto application logic. Now that it is totally separated, somebody would deliberately add \ndependencies to above layers. Developer would notice that he has to do some extra work \nto get some strange dependency. At that moment developer would ask himself or someone \nelse that is this dependency ok. If he would check layered architecture, developer would \nnotice that it violates that. In addition to layered architecture view and communication to \nothers it could be checked during nightly build are dependencies valid.'),(17,'<h3>Persisting domain model objects</h3>\nThe client requests the server to update page DTO \ninstance with modi?ed data. The server calls Hibernate4GWT to merge the current \npersistence Page object with updated data inside the page DTO object. Hibernate4GWT \nloads persistence object and updates changed ?elds and returns a database entity object \nto be used while saving modi?ed data to the database. Page DAO handles only database \nobjects and can now persists data to the database. Once a persisted object is transferred \nback to the client side it is ?rst cloned with Hibernate4GWT to a PageDTO object, which \ncan be serialized all the way to the client side.'),(19,'Requirement suggest that when line is dragged from one point line is having more middle points <p>\n\nIdea is to have a polyline and draw all of those. Below a desired effect is shown with three arrows</p>\n<ul>\n<li> shape is stored as text into database => no need in the future to add new database types, nodetype, shape, text\n<li> line shape is a list of points\n<li> parse text shape\n</ul>\n\n\n'),(48,'<h3>My Design</h3>\nThis is a description.\n\n'),(53,'<h3>New Sketches</h3> \n[[SKETCHES(Title,modifier,modifiedTime,max:5,order:modifiedTime desc,where:createdTime>%NOW%-60*24*5)]] \n\n<h3>Latest Modified Sketches</h3> \n[[SKETCHES(Title,Status,modifier,modifiedTime,max:5,order:modifiedTime desc)]] \n\n'),(54,'<h3>New Sketches</h3> \n[[SKETCHES(id,summary,modifier,modifiedTime, max:3,order:modifiedTime desc,where:createdTime>%NOW%-60*24*3)]] \n\n<h3>Latest Modified Sketches</h3> \n[[SKETCHES(id,summary,link,modifier,modifiedTime, max:5,order:modifiedTime desc)]] \n\n'),(56,'This is a dasboard for Sketcho demo project. \n\n<h3>Goals of the design</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Easily updatable\n<li>Clear structure\n<li>Simple and flexible\n</ul>\n\n\n\n'),(58,'<ul>\n<li>Project\'s are associated to users</li>\n<li>Owner has in addition an admin rights for a project</li>\n</ul>\n\nAll the users have ROLE_USER. ROLE_SUPERUSER can be used later add super user a possibility to access any project he wants. Currently that is not possible.<p>\n\nSecurity always checks if user has rights for a project. No other object\'s are currently associated to projects. But project can be accessed currently most of the domain model objects.</p><p>\n\nACL security is divided in to two different parts. Before method invocation to check if user has rights to access domain object <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong>. After invocation ACL rights are checked with <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong> and <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong>.</p>\n\nUI needs to be improved exclude buttons like edit and delete if user doesn\'t have access rights to action.'),(60,'<ul>\n<li>Project\'s are associated to users</li>\n<li>Owner has in addition an admin rights for a project</li>\n</ul>\n\nAll the users have ROLE_USER. ROLE_SUPERUSER can be used later add super user a possibility to access any project he wants. Currently that is not possible.<p>\n\nSecurity always checks if user has rights for a project. No other object\'s are currently associated to projects. But project can be accessed currently most of the domain model objects.</p><p>\n\nACL security is divided in to two different parts. Before method invocation to check if user has rights to access domain object <strong>AclEntryAfterInvocationProjectPublicProvider</strong>. After invocation ACL rights are checked with <strong>AclEntryAfterInvocationProjectCollectionFilteringProvider</strong> and <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong>.</p>'),(63,'There are only few compulsory fields. '),(65,'This is a template structure for a project. Will be providing dashboard with SKETCH macros. Add first component to a software hierarchy.'),(70,'<ul>\n<li>It needs to be possible to open plain content directly with link. \n</li><li>Needs to have security. Content project is checked if user have authorization for it.\n</li>\n</ul>\n\nSketch could be a page with properties. Properties are content items. <p>\n\nAuthorization while opening Content can be handled with bi-directional association between Sketch and Content.</p>\n\n<pre><code>\n&lt;bean id=\"sketchContentServiceSecurity\" class=\"org.acegisecurity.intercept.method.aopalliance.MethodSecurityInterceptor\"&gt; \n	&lt;property name=\"authenticationManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"authenticationManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"accessDecisionManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"authorizationDecisionManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"afterInvocationManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"afterInvocationManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"objectDefinitionSource\"&gt; \n		&lt;value&gt; \n			net.st.shareddesign.serverAPI.remote.IContentRemote.open=ACL_SKETCH_CONTENT_WRITE\n		&lt;/value&gt; \n	&lt;/property&gt; \n&lt;/bean&gt; \n</ref></ref></ref></code>\n</pre>'),(76,'<strong>SurfaceHandler</strong> is an own widget which listens mouseup, mousedown and mousemove events. With these events moving and resizing is handled.'),(77,'This is a dashboard. Going fine! Excellent. Hoka. hoi'),(80,'If diagram item sends events and canvas which is  a rectangle which sends events. Only top item can send events. Cannot really move items properly. '),(82,'Currently implemented with dojo cometd and bayeaux java servlet. Could connect to another server for server push services. This would also be a load balancing. ContentService can then request from another server active users for a project an notifies those that content update is available. Client would request content update if content is currently viewed on the client side.'),(93,'It needs to be possible to change content size. While editing a model current size area might not be enough. '),(98,''),(100,'Sketches are pages, which have template fields. <strong>properties</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>deletable\n</li><li>\n</li></ul>\n\n\n<h4>Pros</h4>\nCould utilize existing <strong>PageController</strong> and <strong>PageView</strong> implementations. It would reduce bugs if there is same implementation for both sketches and pages. More testing for same implementation.\n\n<h4>Cons</h4>\n\n<h4>Impact</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Macro adapter: etsii oikean nimisiä contentteja\n</li><li>Ticket db entity removed. One possibility is to \n</li><li>Page has type: sketch, doc\n</li><li>Content kuuluu aina pagelle. Voidaan helpommin debugata jos jotain menee pieleen.\n</li><li>Contentilla, modified, created ajat ja kuka muutti.\n</li><li>Kaikkia contentteja ei voi deletoida. Default kenttiä\n</li><li>Miten hanskataan ListContent: tälle pitää pystyä antamaan arvoja. SketchController voi antaa uudelle sketchille nämä arvot. Tälle voi tehdä jonkin taulun myöhemmin. Mitä voi sitten säätää esim. settingsien kautta.\n</li>\n<li>contentin nimen kirjoitus mahdollisuus? Näin pystyisi sketchiin kirjoittamaan uusia elementtejä, joita käyttämään Macro adapterissa. Jos nimeä ei löydy macro adapteri voi nämä ignoroida.\n</li><li>Tulisi vielä harkita, että Content on yleinen tyyppi tietokannassa. Ajonaikana siitä instantioidaan uusia oikeita instansseja... Tämän muutoksen voi kuitenkin tehdä myöhemminkin. Ei ole vaikea tehdä tuosta migraatiota. Jos <strong>performanssi</strong> alkaa kärsimään on tähän mentävä.\n</li><li>Contentilla vois olla name visibility, näin otsikko kenttä näytetään tavallisillakin sivuilla. Otsikon nimellä voidaan sitten myöhemmin kopioida/imporoida contenttia muille sivuille.\n</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>SketchController antaa contentit view:lle, joka vaan näyttää ja välittää eventit takaisin contollerille,\n\nIf page content has name, then page is showing that with h2.</p>\n\n<p>Page name sketchi-tapauksessa voisi olla vaikka vain id ja nameVisibility = false.\n\n</p><p><strong>Content Property Change Listener</strong>. Tällä vois dynaamisesti kuunnella jos jokin property editor contentissa muuttuu. Näin voitaisiin poistaa IPageOrderedContent ja IContentilla olisi propertyjä.\n</p><p><strong>Security</strong>. Remember to update secure methods! e.g. IPageRemote::createPage.\n\n</p><p>Pageen voidaan tallentaa viimeisin muutosaika ja oikeastaan alkuun tämä riittää, mutta contentti tulee tarvitsemaan myös created | modified kentät. Contenteilla tulee olla omat historiat ja versiot.\n\n</p><p>Vaihtoehtoja nimetyille contenteille. \n</p><ul>\n<li>Haetaan map contenteista serveriltä erikseen. loadMap(content, map); name, value pair list comes back.  <br><strong>Map&lt;String, String&gt; loadNamedContentItems(page, List&lt;String&gt; namedItems)</strong>\n<br>Tässä on etuna se, että ei vahingossa ladata koko kantaa.\n</li><li>non lazy content items erikseen ja content päätyy tähän listaan, jos lazy param on true. Vähän hankala kun contentteja on tämän jälkeen kahdessa eri taulussa. Tosin tämä voisi olla performanssinkin kannalta nopeampaa...\n</li></ul>\n\n<p></p><h4>Poistettavaa</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>db and dto Ticket\n</li><li>ticket controller ja view ja constantit\n</li></ul>'),(102,''),(107,'Start dragging background and all items will move with it.'),(112,'Sketches are pages, which have template fields. <strong>properties</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>deletable\n</li><li>\n</li></ul>\n\n\n<h4>Pros</h4>\nCould utilize existing <strong>PageController</strong> and <strong>PageView</strong> implementations. It would reduce bugs if there is same implementation for both sketches and pages. More testing for same implementation.\n\n<h4>Cons</h4>\n\n<h4>Impact</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Macro adapter: etsii oikean nimisiä contentteja\n</li><li>Ticket db entity removed. One possibility is to \n</li><li>Page has type: sketch, doc\n</li><li>Content kuuluu aina pagelle. Voidaan helpommin debugata jos jotain menee pieleen.\n</li><li>Contentilla, modified, created ajat ja kuka muutti.\n</li><li>Kaikkia contentteja ei voi deletoida. Default kenttiä\n</li><li>Miten hanskataan ListContent: tälle pitää pystyä antamaan arvoja. SketchController voi antaa uudelle sketchille nämä arvot. Tälle voi tehdä jonkin taulun myöhemmin. Mitä voi sitten säätää esim. settingsien kautta.\n</li>\n<li>contentin nimen kirjoitus mahdollisuus? Näin pystyisi sketchiin kirjoittamaan uusia elementtejä, joita käyttämään Macro adapterissa. Jos nimeä ei löydy macro adapteri voi nämä ignoroida.\n</li><li>Tulisi vielä harkita, että Content on yleinen tyyppi tietokannassa. Ajonaikana siitä instantioidaan uusia oikeita instansseja... Tämän muutoksen voi kuitenkin tehdä myöhemminkin. Ei ole vaikea tehdä tuosta migraatiota. Jos <strong>performanssi</strong> alkaa kärsimään on tähän mentävä.\n</li><li>Contentilla vois olla name visibility, näin otsikko kenttä näytetään tavallisillakin sivuilla. Otsikon nimellä voidaan sitten myöhemmin kopioida/imporoida contenttia muille sivuille.\n</li></ul>\n\n\n<p>SketchController antaa contentit view:lle, joka vaan näyttää ja välittää eventit takaisin contollerille,\n\nIf page content has name, then page is showing that with h2.</p>\n\n<p>Page name sketchi-tapauksessa voisi olla vaikka vain id ja nameVisibility = false.\n\n</p><p><strong>Content Property Change Listener</strong>. Tällä vois dynaamisesti kuunnella jos jokin property editor contentissa muuttuu. Näin voitaisiin poistaa IPageOrderedContent ja IContentilla olisi propertyjä.\n</p><p><strong>Security</strong>. Remember to update secure methods! e.g. IPageRemote::createPage.\n\n</p><p>Pageen voidaan tallentaa viimeisin muutosaika ja oikeastaan alkuun tämä riittää, mutta contentti tulee tarvitsemaan myös created | modified kentät. Contenteilla tulee olla omat historiat ja versiot.\n\n</p><p>Vaihtoehtoja nimetyille contenteille. \n</p><ul>\n<li>Haetaan map contenteista serveriltä erikseen. loadMap(content, map); name, value pair list comes back.  <br><strong>Map&lt;String, String&gt; loadNamedContentItems(page, List&lt;String&gt; namedItems)</strong>\n<br>Tässä on etuna se, että ei vahingossa ladata koko kantaa.\n</li><li>non lazy content items erikseen ja content päätyy tähän listaan, jos lazy param on true. Vähän hankala kun contentteja on tämän jälkeen kahdessa eri taulussa. Tosin tämä voisi olla performanssinkin kannalta nopeampaa...\n</li></ul>\n\n<p></p><h4>Poistettavaa</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>db and dto Ticket\n</li><li>ticket controller ja view ja constantit\n</li></ul>\n'),(117,'<ul>\n<li>It needs to be possible to open plain content directly with link. \n</li><li>Needs to have security. Content project is checked if user have authorization for it.\n</li>\n</ul>\n\nSketch could be a page with properties. Properties are content items. <p>\n\nAuthorization while opening Content can be handled with bi-directional association between Sketch and Content.</p>\n\n<pre><code>\n&lt;bean id=\"sketchContentServiceSecurity\" class=\"org.acegisecurity.intercept.method.aopalliance.MethodSecurityInterceptor\"&gt; \n	&lt;property name=\"authenticationManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"authenticationManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"accessDecisionManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"authorizationDecisionManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"afterInvocationManager\"&gt;<ref bean=\"afterInvocationManager\"> \n	&lt;property name=\"objectDefinitionSource\"&gt; \n		&lt;value&gt; \n			net.st.shareddesign.serverAPI.remote.IContentRemote.open=ACL_SKETCH_CONTENT_WRITE\n		&lt;/value&gt; \n	&lt;/property&gt; \n&lt;/bean&gt; \n</ref></ref></ref></code>\n</pre>'),(122,'It needs to be possible to change content size. While editing a model current size area might not be enough. '),(127,'<ul>\n<li>Project\'s are associated to users</li>\n<li>Owner has in addition an admin rights for a project</li>\n</ul>\n\nAll the users have ROLE_USER. ROLE_SUPERUSER can be used later add super user a possibility to access any project he wants. Currently that is not possible.<p>\n\nSecurity always checks if user has rights for a project. No other object\'s are currently associated to projects. But project can be accessed currently most of the domain model objects.</p><p>\n\nACL security is divided in to two different parts. Before method invocation to check if user has rights to access domain object <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong>. After invocation ACL rights are checked with <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong> and <strong>AclProjectEntryVoter</strong>.</p>\n\nUI needs to be improved exclude buttons like edit and delete if user doesn\'t have access rights to action.'),(130,'This is text for below one'),(134,'Giving excellent description'),(139,'Sketchillä on ainoastaan pari ominaisuutta: delete, page name, siirto design puolelle (tämän voi tehdä vasta seuraavaan releasiin). Sketchiä ei voi järjestää... tai miksi ei voisi. Ainoastaa pää sketchit olisi näkyvissä tai plussalla avattavissa.'),(144,NULL),(152,'User have a need to save how UI is personalized. E.g. saving is project members disclosure panel open or closed... is Design Map open or closed. How editing happens one click or two clicks.'),(154,'<h3>Current real model</h3>\nCurrent real model. E.g. in this situation I might like to move previous domain model to sketch side. That could be e.g. drag and dropped to sketches link and then it would be applied to sketches. In this situation toolbar should move with the. This is the specialization that Sketcho has for design. Real usability for quick designs and keeping documentation uptodate.'),(158,'Feedback flow'),(163,NULL),(168,'When macro [column] is inserted. Everything after that goes to separate column.'),(173,'Ei olisikaan erillistä [edit] -linkkiä vaan esim. klikkaamalla kenttää kenttä muuttuu editoitavaksi. Tallennus tapahtuu automaattisesti kun focus muuttuu. Käyttäjä alkaa navigoimaan muuaalle tai siirtää fokuksen pois selaimesta. Tai alkuun voi olla esim. tuplaklikkaus, jolla voi siirtyä edit-modeen tai edit-linkki voi edelleen olla...'),(178,'Ei enää erillistä sketchi macroa viimeksi muokatuille vaan kaikki on samassa listassa ja voidaan määrittää mikä tulkitaan uudeksi. Uudet sketchit erotellaan erikseen ikonilla.\n\n<h4>Discarded</h4>\nFeature is discarded and now status is defining if sketch is new or not. Style is set based on style.'),(183,'Currently sketches view and sketches macro performance is not on a good level. Perhaps Map database solution is not correct, because it is so slow or pipe from client to server is blocked by cometd...\n\n<h5>Future</h5>\nCurrently performance is ok. Might be needed to future cache and load only 25 items at a time.'),(188,'Server would notify when project is changed. Then project would not need to be updated every time project is changed. On the client side there could be state object that listens project change notifies and other objects requests that through context.'),(198,'Refactor page title content to be a page name. This would be same for sketch and pages. Page title needs to be modifiable in same way as page content is usually modified.'),(202,NULL),(207,'Diagram items with text (boxes, ellipses) will be auto resized when long text is inputted. If user edits size should size be that then and auto resize is off? Or it is just possible to resize box, but if text is modified size is changed again. At least that could be the first approach and no changes to the model is needed.\n\n<p>Below is shown possible design when user sizing is remembered.'),(211,'In this way for one project can have own custom values as choice items. Could be possible to sort based on the value and change options for existing sketches. \n\n<h3>Proposal</h3>\nFor now let\'s just have one order column which is modified time and background color of Closed are grey.'),(215,'Selected relationship is selected on toolbar area.'),(219,'Sketches would be shown in the same way in a project dashboard and on a sketches view. SketchUiList needs to override addRow method and add row customization in there.'),(223,'User clicks needs to be diminished when modeled. Currently it is not very intuitive to add new element types from a toolbar to modeling area. Usability tests have shown that it is difficult to understand how to get elements from the toolbar to the modeling area. \n\n<h5>Solution</h5>\nAdd feature direct insert the toolbar. Selected item will be directly inserted to the modeling area when clicked. Item will be drawn on that position. Double clicking will be supported as well. This could be later configurable. \n\n<h5>Note</h5>\nIf there are any items selected in the main modeling area, item will not be copied on first click, instead first selection will go away and second click will copy selected item from the toolbar area.'),(227,'Sketches can be ordered by creation time in that way. An other possibility would be to add creation time column.'),(231,'Implemented in <a href=\"http://7scales.net:8080/sketcho/#?controller=sketch&projectId=1&pageId=46\">Bending relationship is totally non intuitive!!</a>. Handles can be eaten by dragging on forward point.'),(235,'Bend points needs to be created by dragging or key combination needs to be ctrl plus mouse down point. Below diagram unfortunately only works on Safari. When keyboard events are routed through browser. This model would support automatically client keyboard layout.\n\n<p>\nFor bending it has been decided to remove special key to start bending. \n<ul>\n<li>Bending happends through handles that are crosses or squares (at least on background those needs to be squares)\n<li>Bend points are deletable. Changed that when those is straightened then new bend points just disappears.\n<li>Relationships can be moved on any other points. (draggable as a whole)\n</ul>\n\n<b>Different line strategies</b>\n<ul>\n<li>lines are separate own lines (could be easier)\n<li>lines are polylines (graphics might be faster). Slightly more difficult to calculate where is middle point to start bending. Difficult to calculate selection area! <strong>This approach has been selected.</strong>\n</ul>'),(239,'It could fix key event problems on safari 4 where shift and cntrl events on top of silverlight plugin cannot be catched. Also IE8 support is added. Beware that ie8 has own user agent value if silverlight plugin loading needs some special hacking...'),(243,'Could be sorted based on priority. Drag and drop support to change priority can be added easily. But big lists might bring some problems... Priority is modified only through drag and dropping. This is then a working backlog list of design work items. This is important feature, because in agile methodologies work items are prioritized. There should be handle on the left side as gmail has for applying labels. Handle would be used to change priority in the list.\n\n<p>\nOne possibility is to prioritize based on Status and modified time. Then priorities are only groups which might be enough. Status values would need to be in priority order. Then list need to have separate order value and display name. Order would be New, Started, Accepted, Designed, Future, Discarded. '),(247,'Needs color change support from ui and domain model. This is also needed for version comparison. It should be possible to show which elements are added on which version.'),(251,NULL),(257,NULL),(265,NULL),(271,NULL),(277,'<ul>\n<li>Especially drawing on linux platform is slow and picture is updated only when mouse is released. This makes drawing really hard on Linux environment.\n<li>An other problem is that relationships are updated when something is moved. All relationships are redrawn. Need to change observer model that elements registers directly to an other element and not controlled through central mouse manager...\n</ul>\n\n\n<h5>Possible solution</h5>\nChange rendering so that position is not set immediately only after render transformation. This means coordinate translation, which is harder to use otherwise generally.\n\n<h5>Consider this</h5>\nAll the elements could just handled with transformations. Then there would not be any flickering when mouse is released. When editor is saved transformations would be applied to be actual position of a shape. Then flickering would arise only during saving.\n\n<h5>Performance problems still!!</h5>\nOne possibility could be that dojo is slowing performance with silverlight. Put own dojo wrapper before silverlight and see if there is a performance differences.\nMost probably problem is with relationships. Those are redrawn way too often and taking too much processing power. New observer model is needed or anchor is checked before updated.\nNeed to still study transformations for polylines. Is it possible to have transformation instead setting shape, because that is also sligthly heavy...\n\n<h5>Silverlight rendering problems still</h5>\nIt seems that relationship rendering is slow. Perhaps applyTransform could be optimized to modify only lines, but no selection areas.\n\n<h5>Silverlight rendering problems improved</h5>\nProblem is that silverlight doesn\'t get turn to render if javascript takes all processing power. Now DeferredCommand increment command is added to do drawing steps on mouse move managers. This makes drawing little bit funny on slow machines, because elements are drawn separately and that is clearly seen. Following guide lines are used: <a href=\"http://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/bb693295.aspx#transparent_control\">Performance improvement guide lines for Silverlight</a>. Especially silverlight visibility (dojo impl removed) and incremental javascript processing are used.\n\n\n'),(290,'Olisi oikeastaan aika tärkeätä pystyä lisäämään uutta tietoa kommentteina, jolloin päivämäärä näkyy erikseen ja kuka kommentin on lisännyt. Kommenttia ei pystyisi muuttamaan myöhemmin (ehkä käyttäjä itse...). Itse käytän tiedon lisäämistä inkrementaalisesti ja samoin kävisi myös useamman käyttäjän käyttäessä sketchoa. Tässä tulisi ehkä miettiä voiko kontenttia aina vaan muokata kontentin omistaja...'),(296,'Relationship needs to attach itself to an element easier. Elements which allow anchors need to provide dynamic anchor positions. When relationship is released on top of anchor element, element decides shortest anchor position in its edge and reports that to anchor. Anchor can then attach itself to there. This however doesn\'t work if anchor element size is changed. Size change would need in addition to support anchor elements within element. Then if these anchor elements within element is moved only then onDrag for anchor element would be notified.'),(305,'Niin paljon on erilaisia kenttiä, että niitä tulee kuitenkin lisää. Jokaisella domain elementillä tulisi olla oma property-taulu. Kun properteillä on tyyppi, niin UI:ssa voidaan luoda oikeanlainen UI-komponentti.'),(309,'Niin paljon on erilaisia kenttiä, että niitä tulee kuitenkin lisää. Eri hoivataloilla on kuitenkin jotain omaa. Jokaisella domain elementillä tulisi olla oma property-taulu. Kun properteillä on tyyppi, niin UI:ssa voidaan luoda oikeanlainen UI-komponentti.\n'),(312,'<h5>Kartanonväki yleisiä vaatimuksia</h5>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Printtaus jokaisesta näkymästä.\n<li>Asukaslistaus\n<li>Tietojen suojaus (pankkiturvallisuus)\n<li>Client-Server\n<li>Ulkomaalaiset (venäläiset, filippiiniläiset) => lokalisointi\n<li>Käytettävyys\n<li>Search\n</ul>\n\nTyön tulisi valmistua 1 1/2 vuodessa => 2011 Q1. Lisäosien tekeminen. Asiakkuuden hallinta. Laskutus. Perustoiminnallisuus on hoivaseuranta. Lisää on vielä hälytykset.\n\n<p>Kilpailijoita: raisoft, hoivasofta..., enterra...\n\n<p>Oikea turvallisuustaso. Voidaanko sertifikaateilla lisätä turvallisuutta? Avain+salasanayhdistelmä. Varmaankin riittävä turvallisuus saataisiin sisäverkko+vpn yhteys+kriittisen datan kryptaus'),(316,'Issuena voi olla bugi, enhancement, refactoring, comment. Näitä kuitenkin voi muuttaa vain projektin omistaja. Prioriteettia pitää pystyä muuttamaan esim. raahaamalla. Description. Commentit alas. \n\n<p>\nPicture linkit onnistuukin rich text editorissa vaan includoi imagen.'),(321,'Take existing framework design from Sketcho.'),(324,'<ul>\n<li>List => drop down selection\n<li>String => String field\n<li>Number => Number field\n<li>Boolean => boolean field\n</ul>'),(326,'TODO: how to handle option values!! Those could be loaded or provided at the same time with DTO objects with some logic. Jos options_class on tyhjä niin options kenttä sisältää tarvittavat vaihtoehdot. Jos options_class sisältää luokan niin silloin options arvo täytetään dynaamisesti tämän mukaan.'),(329,'It is possible to create page from element with in diagram editor area.'),(333,NULL),(337,NULL),(345,''),(349,'');
